Global and local economic factors. We obtain monthly values for the total imports and total exports of the United Kingdom and the United States. We translate these figures to pounds, sum all four series, and use log differences measured from
   \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} \newcommand\cyr{ \renewcommand\rmdefault{wncyr} \renewcommand\sfdefault{wncyss} \renewcommand\encodingdefault{OT2} \normalfont \selectfont} \DeclareTextFontCommand{\textcyr}{\cyr} \pagestyle{empty} \DeclareMathSizes{10}{9}{7}{6} \begin{document} \landscape $t-12$ \end{document}
totas a proxy for world economic growth (Chen1991). Lacking an indicator that aggregates all countries and all types of economic activity, the sum of inward and outward trade for the United Kingdom and the United States seems a reasonable proxy. We also obtain annual data on trade flows and price indexes for China and Netherlands Indies and annual data on trade flows only for the Straits Settlements.15Because these series are only available at an annual frequency, they are not used in our asset pricing test but in a subsequent exploration of silver’s power to forecast basic economic indicators.
